1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,553
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,553 --> 00:00:03,036
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,513 --> 00:00:05,939
(Episode 30)

4
00:00:13,660 --> 00:00:14,660
Honey.

5
00:00:16,860 --> 00:00:18,218
You must be really shocked.

6
00:00:18,360 --> 00:00:20,153
What happened was...

7
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:22,760
What are you doing here? Why are you...

8
00:00:23,860 --> 00:00:25,860
I was actually going to tell you
everything today.

9
00:00:26,593 --> 00:00:28,460
The truth is...

10
00:00:30,359 --> 00:00:32,263
Am I still drunk from yesterday?

11
00:00:33,960 --> 00:00:36,360
Why is an executive director
from Samho Group here?

12
00:00:36,813 --> 00:00:38,505
Sir.

13
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:40,874
Someone spilled a drink over there.
Please clean it quickly.

14
00:00:41,260 --> 00:00:42,630
- Hurry.
- Yes, understood.

15
00:00:43,760 --> 00:00:45,546
I'll be there soon,
so go wait at that cafe.

16
00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:47,248
I'll explain everything. Wait for me.

17
00:01:04,431 --> 00:01:08,068
Looks like that real estate lady's husband
works as a cleaner at our company.

18
00:01:08,920 --> 00:01:10,070
Seems that way.

19
00:01:11,313 --> 00:01:13,473
And she acted all high and mighty
despite that?

20
00:01:14,793 --> 00:01:16,176
What do you mean, "despite that?"

21
00:01:16,552 --> 00:01:19,660
The cleaning staff are employees
of this company too.

22
00:01:19,660 --> 00:01:20,660
Who said they weren't?

23
00:01:21,893 --> 00:01:24,084
But it seems like Kang Yeon Ja...

24
00:01:24,393 --> 00:01:26,920
didn't know what her husband did
for a living.

25
00:01:27,493 --> 00:01:29,289
She looked pretty shocked.

26
00:01:29,793 --> 00:01:32,459
So what? You want us
to go comfort her or something?

27
00:01:33,293 --> 00:01:35,996
No, I'm just a little worried.

28
00:01:37,371 --> 00:01:39,066
Acting all pretentious with her French,

29
00:01:39,066 --> 00:01:41,535
babbling on like she's so impressive.
Seriously.

30
00:01:54,193 --> 00:01:57,851
Right. I drank too much yesterday.

31
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:02,519
I must've been hallucinating.

32
00:02:05,993 --> 00:02:08,195
Taxi! Wait!

33
00:02:10,593 --> 00:02:11,593
Honey!

34
00:02:14,140 --> 00:02:15,235
Honey!

35
00:02:25,293 --> 00:02:27,593
Hey, Eun Nim. Are you home right now?

36
00:02:29,132 --> 00:02:30,250
Good.

37
00:02:30,493 --> 00:02:33,453
Your mom saw me in my cleaning uniform
and was shocked.

38
00:02:33,453 --> 00:02:36,489
She just got in a taxi
and is probably heading home now.

39
00:02:36,693 --> 00:02:38,025
Please calm her down.

40
00:02:39,372 --> 00:02:41,072
I'll just change my clothes
and head over right away.

41
00:02:41,799 --> 00:02:43,999
Okay. Please take care of your mom.

42
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:48,168
(Eun Ae)

43
00:02:50,013 --> 00:02:51,638
I shouldn't call Eun Ae. She must be busy.

44
00:03:06,285 --> 00:03:07,785
Drink some water, Mom.

45
00:03:15,206 --> 00:03:17,297
Do you want to lie down?
Should I spread out the bedding?

46
00:03:19,326 --> 00:03:23,360
Do you know something by any chance?

47
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:25,105
What? Know what?

48
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:28,475
No. Just get out.

49
00:03:28,475 --> 00:03:29,804
Okay.

50
00:03:30,260 --> 00:03:32,112
I'll be outside,
so call me if you need anything.

51
00:03:34,793 --> 00:03:36,016
This makes no sense.

52
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:38,185
What in the world...

53
00:03:41,812 --> 00:03:44,450
Our team's retirement community concept...

54
00:03:44,770 --> 00:03:46,893
is a comfortable home
in harmony with nature,

55
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:49,162
where people come first
and companionship thrives.

56
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:51,367
- One moment, Team Manager.
- Yes?

57
00:03:52,060 --> 00:03:53,960
You seem too stiff.

58
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:56,837
Your expression is rigid,
and your tone sounds a little formal.

59
00:03:57,698 --> 00:04:00,173
How about making eye contact
with the judges...

60
00:04:00,173 --> 00:04:03,714
and speaking more comfortably,
like you're having a conversation?

61
00:04:04,993 --> 00:04:07,935
Eun Ae, our Team Manager is a veteran.

62
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:10,350
I think it's a bit much for an intern
to criticize him like that.

63
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,780
No, she's right. I'll try again.

64
00:04:18,791 --> 00:04:21,191
Our team's retirement community concept...

65
00:04:21,191 --> 00:04:22,193
(Eun Nim)

66
00:04:22,193 --> 00:04:24,498
is a comfortable home
in harmony with nature,

67
00:04:25,260 --> 00:04:27,734
where people come first
and companionship thrives.

68
00:04:31,746 --> 00:04:32,746
Okay.

69
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:40,180
What's wrong? I'm a little busy right now.

70
00:04:41,660 --> 00:04:45,018
What? Mom? What about Dad?

71
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:48,788
Call Eun Hyeong quickly. Hurry.

72
00:04:49,860 --> 00:04:50,960
What should we do with Mom?

73
00:04:52,660 --> 00:04:55,195
What's wrong? Did something happen?

74
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,198
No, it's nothing. I'll go back in now.

75
00:04:58,859 --> 00:05:01,635
Looks like something happened at home.
You should clock out.

76
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:03,904
No, it's okay.

77
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:06,460
Your face says otherwise.

78
00:05:06,460 --> 00:05:07,460
Hurry and go.

79
00:05:08,060 --> 00:05:09,476
But the presentation
is just around the corner...

80
00:05:09,476 --> 00:05:11,378
I'll take responsibility
for this presentation.

81
00:05:11,793 --> 00:05:13,560
During the second round
of the competition,

82
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:15,015
you make sure
Joy's power really shines through.

83
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:16,516
Thank you, Team Manager.

84
00:05:20,579 --> 00:05:21,955
What happened this time?

85
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,960
I'll head out first.

86
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:31,493
Why? Is something wrong?

87
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:34,067
No, I'll get going now.

88
00:05:40,893 --> 00:05:42,075
What is this?

89
00:05:42,345 --> 00:05:45,045
The atmosphere between you two
feels subtly different somehow.

90
00:05:45,519 --> 00:05:46,560
What?

91
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,348
Until recently,
it felt like you were enemies...

92
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:50,960
No, you seemed more like rivals,

93
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:52,419
but now it feels different.

94
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:55,760
Are you saying I felt rivalry
toward Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

95
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:57,490
No, I mean... Forget I said that.

96
00:05:57,860 --> 00:06:01,795
Then again,
rivals are supposed to be equals, right?

97
00:06:08,460 --> 00:06:09,836
Are you confident about the presentation?

98
00:06:10,152 --> 00:06:11,838
Why? Do I not look confident?

99
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:15,008
I've never once thought
our team would lose.

100
00:06:16,193 --> 00:06:19,412
Where does all that baseless confidence
come from?

101
00:06:20,186 --> 00:06:21,986
Because Seo Seung Ri is on my team.

102
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:25,952
Anyway, make sure you win.

103
00:06:25,952 --> 00:06:28,360
Okay. I absolutely won't disappoint you.

104
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,493
If our team wins this competition,

105
00:06:31,493 --> 00:06:32,859
grant me just one wish.

106
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:34,494
A wish?

107
00:06:34,494 --> 00:06:37,530
Don't worry. It's something really small.

108
00:06:38,413 --> 00:06:39,793
Promise me you'll grant it.

109
00:06:39,793 --> 00:06:42,869
Then I'll really give it my all
and show you what I can do.

110
00:06:44,413 --> 00:06:46,406
Let's talk about that after we win.

111
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:54,779
At first,
I think the biggest reason was...

112
00:06:54,779 --> 00:06:56,149
that I didn't want to disappoint you.

113
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:59,291
You spent your whole life
thinking only about our family.

114
00:07:02,005 --> 00:07:05,677
Things were getting better,
and you could finally relax,

115
00:07:06,060 --> 00:07:07,391
so I just couldn't bring myself
to tell you.

116
00:07:10,293 --> 00:07:13,290
So I thought,
even if it wasn't something satisfying,

117
00:07:14,193 --> 00:07:15,860
I should at least find a job...

118
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:20,080
that wouldn't disappoint you too much
before telling you.

119
00:07:22,093 --> 00:07:23,643
But even that wasn't easy.

120
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:30,664
Every time you said I smelled like bleach,

121
00:07:31,793 --> 00:07:34,654
I kept thinking, "I should tell her"...

122
00:07:34,893 --> 00:07:38,925
And you kept deceiving me for over a year?

123
00:07:39,273 --> 00:07:40,829
You think that's an excuse?

124
00:07:40,829 --> 00:07:44,455
I'm not making excuses right now.
I'm telling you how I felt all this time.

125
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:46,529
And in the middle of all that,
Eun Ae, Eun Hyeong,

126
00:07:46,529 --> 00:07:48,969
and even Eun Nim's issues
all exploded one after another.

127
00:07:48,969 --> 00:07:49,970
Then what about...

128
00:07:51,239 --> 00:07:54,206
the salary that kept getting deposited
into our account every month without fail?

129
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:01,948
Severance pay from Samho.

130
00:08:03,212 --> 00:08:05,752
What? Severance pay?

131
00:08:07,293 --> 00:08:08,973
You've been splitting up
your severance pay...

132
00:08:08,973 --> 00:08:10,906
and depositing it into our account
every month like it was a salary?

133
00:08:13,639 --> 00:08:15,228
- Where's Mom?
- In the room.

134
00:08:16,179 --> 00:08:17,179
How...

135
00:08:18,293 --> 00:08:20,822
How could you deceive me so completely?

136
00:08:21,860 --> 00:08:24,381
Were you always
someone who could lie this thoroughly?

137
00:08:24,860 --> 00:08:26,588
Are you really...

138
00:08:27,486 --> 00:08:29,409
the Cho Seong Jun I know?

139
00:08:30,793 --> 00:08:32,712
This won't do. We should go in too.

140
00:08:40,860 --> 00:08:43,651
Dad ended up like this because of us.

141
00:08:44,040 --> 00:08:45,892
It's because
we still haven't settled down properly.

142
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:48,917
That's right, Mom.

143
00:08:49,206 --> 00:08:52,966
Dad's suffered so much emotionally
and physically all this time.

144
00:08:53,493 --> 00:08:55,702
He tried over and over to tell you,

145
00:08:56,060 --> 00:08:58,460
but every time, we caused another problem.

146
00:08:59,399 --> 00:09:01,474
Don't be mad at Dad, Mom.

147
00:09:01,860 --> 00:09:03,877
It's not like he wanted to lose his job.

148
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:06,213
Then you all...

149
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:09,253
You all knew your dad lost his job
this whole time?

150
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,360
Since when?

151
00:09:11,693 --> 00:09:13,286
For me, only recently.

152
00:09:13,593 --> 00:09:15,722
We also found out recently by chance.

153
00:09:22,806 --> 00:09:25,432
So once again,
I was the only one who didn't know!

154
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,002
Am I really your mom?

155
00:09:29,732 --> 00:09:30,760
Honey.

156
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:32,760
Am I really your wife?

157
00:09:35,260 --> 00:09:38,645
Am I even part of this family?

158
00:09:40,460 --> 00:09:41,993
I can't stand the sight of any of you,
so get out.

159
00:09:42,393 --> 00:09:43,750
Mom, please.

160
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,752
Can't you hear me? Get out!

161
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:49,422
You all leave.
I'll talk to your mom alone.

162
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:52,492
No, I have nothing to say to you either.
You get out first!

163
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:58,013
No, apparently I was the only one here
who wasn't family.

164
00:09:58,013 --> 00:10:00,800
I'm the one who should leave.

165
00:10:01,499 --> 00:10:04,070
Honey, what's wrong with you?

166
00:10:04,393 --> 00:10:07,474
Mom, please. We were wrong.

167
00:10:07,474 --> 00:10:10,444
Mom, I promise
we'll never hide anything from you again.

168
00:10:10,666 --> 00:10:11,878
Please don't do this.

169
00:10:12,260 --> 00:10:14,447
We were truly wrong, Mom.

170
00:10:15,553 --> 00:10:16,616
Mom.

171
00:10:17,260 --> 00:10:18,318
My goodness.

172
00:10:19,786 --> 00:10:23,256
I've wasted my life.
I've lived my whole life for nothing.

173
00:10:23,986 --> 00:10:27,160
All this time, I lived believing
my family was my everything.

174
00:10:28,213 --> 00:10:31,741
But I was mistaken.

175
00:10:33,413 --> 00:10:36,164
Lying because of me.
Walking on eggshells because of me.

176
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:39,755
If it weren't for me,
you'd all probably be living comfortably.

177
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:44,777
It's all because of me!

178
00:10:45,827 --> 00:10:47,114
Kang Yeon Ja!

179
00:10:47,846 --> 00:10:50,250
That's not true. It's really not.

180
00:10:51,072 --> 00:10:53,887
- Mom, I'm sorry.
- Mom.

181
00:10:54,860 --> 00:10:56,140
Dad...

182
00:11:22,626 --> 00:11:24,551
What?
There was a photo inside the necklace?

183
00:11:25,193 --> 00:11:27,587
Yeah. This morning,
Mother suddenly exploded at me,

184
00:11:27,873 --> 00:11:31,418
asking if I had touched the photo.

185
00:11:32,902 --> 00:11:34,260
So what happened after that?

186
00:11:34,267 --> 00:11:35,972
Then Father suddenly walked in,

187
00:11:35,972 --> 00:11:37,964
sent me out,
and things quieted down after that.

188
00:11:39,206 --> 00:11:40,838
But seriously, it's ridiculous.

189
00:11:40,838 --> 00:11:42,982
I bent over backward for her
until my face cramped up...

190
00:11:42,982 --> 00:11:45,587
because of the remaining 20 percent,

191
00:11:45,587 --> 00:11:47,273
and she treats me like I'm nothing.

192
00:11:48,079 --> 00:11:51,539
Wait. If things quieted down
after Father walked in,

193
00:11:51,919 --> 00:11:54,147
does that mean Father touched the photo?

194
00:11:54,147 --> 00:11:57,584
Or was the photo a secret from Father,

195
00:11:57,584 --> 00:11:59,152
so Mother kept her mouth shut?

196
00:11:59,152 --> 00:12:00,520
I don't know.

197
00:12:01,986 --> 00:12:05,453
Wait a second.
Then the photo inside that necklace...

198
00:12:07,146 --> 00:12:08,246
I think that's it.

199
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:12,300
But the photo Mr. Seo brought
to the hospital room was of a little girl.

200
00:12:12,435 --> 00:12:15,535
Could it be Mother's hidden daughter?

201
00:12:16,916 --> 00:12:20,173
Think about it. So Father's currently...

202
00:12:20,173 --> 00:12:22,275
searching for that child through Mr. Seo.

203
00:12:23,293 --> 00:12:24,677
Then did she lose the child?

204
00:12:24,892 --> 00:12:28,725
Or did she abandon the child
to marry Father?

205
00:12:32,293 --> 00:12:35,455
Before Father passes away,
he's trying to fulfill Mother's wish.

206
00:12:36,787 --> 00:12:38,487
Right. That's it.

207
00:12:39,645 --> 00:12:42,313
Now all the puzzle pieces
finally fit together.

208
00:12:42,313 --> 00:12:43,730
Then what happens now?

209
00:12:44,126 --> 00:12:48,268
If they actually find that child,
does that make her your half-sibling?

210
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,660
- Half-sibling?
- Yeah.

211
00:12:52,066 --> 00:12:54,926
What are you saying?
If Mother gave birth before remarrying,

212
00:12:54,926 --> 00:12:56,993
then the child has nothing to do
with Father.

213
00:12:56,993 --> 00:12:58,611
That's true, but...

214
00:12:58,913 --> 00:13:01,781
if they find that child and add her
to the family registry someday,

215
00:13:02,293 --> 00:13:05,407
whether you share blood or not,
she'll undeniably become Father's child.

216
00:13:05,746 --> 00:13:08,755
Then you'll have to split the inheritance
in half.

217
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:11,090
Half?

218
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:13,459
Of course,
that's assuming they even find her.

219
00:13:14,319 --> 00:13:16,029
But do you think that'll be easy?

220
00:13:16,632 --> 00:13:19,032
If she could've been found,
they would've found her long ago.

221
00:13:19,573 --> 00:13:21,901
They won't find her. No way. Impossible.

222
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:25,293
Still, I honestly never imagined this.

223
00:13:25,293 --> 00:13:28,741
How could our family have such a secret?

224
00:13:28,741 --> 00:13:30,893
See? Just because you're family...

225
00:13:30,893 --> 00:13:33,946
doesn't mean you know everything.

226
00:13:34,786 --> 00:13:39,032
Right. Remember that awful woman...

227
00:13:39,306 --> 00:13:41,020
I told you about
from my line dancing class?

228
00:13:43,073 --> 00:13:44,999
Do you know what happened today?

229
00:13:45,994 --> 00:13:48,118
- That woman's husband is apparently...
- Apparently,

230
00:13:48,993 --> 00:13:51,460
Su Jeong tried to show off
with her French,

231
00:13:51,806 --> 00:13:54,806
but that woman completely humiliated her.

232
00:13:58,239 --> 00:14:02,306
More importantly, that woman's husband
works as a cleaner at Kangsu Construction.

233
00:14:03,393 --> 00:14:04,393
What?

234
00:14:04,393 --> 00:14:08,127
But it looked like she didn't know
what kind of work her husband did.

235
00:14:08,947 --> 00:14:12,666
The moment she saw him in his uniform,
she went completely pale.

236
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:18,458
I still haven't even told my wife
that I lost my job.

237
00:14:18,660 --> 00:14:19,959
And I can't keep hiding it forever.

238
00:14:20,593 --> 00:14:23,522
You're not hiding anything from me, right?

239
00:14:25,593 --> 00:14:29,736
Anyway, the moment trust between husband
and wife breaks, everything turns to dust.

240
00:14:32,393 --> 00:14:35,273
Right. I invited Min Ho over this weekend.

241
00:14:36,227 --> 00:14:38,544
Chief Ko? Why all of a sudden?

242
00:14:39,166 --> 00:14:42,272
Why else? To coach him a little.

243
00:14:43,276 --> 00:14:44,759
What kind of man...

244
00:14:44,759 --> 00:14:46,986
can't win over a woman's heart
for over ten years?

245
00:14:47,112 --> 00:14:49,288
Is he lacking in looks
or family background?

246
00:14:50,593 --> 00:14:53,036
I'm not completely satisfied
with the in-laws,

247
00:14:53,566 --> 00:14:55,333
but it's not like they'll live together
after marriage.

248
00:14:55,866 --> 00:14:58,831
Why are you acting like this these days?

249
00:14:58,932 --> 00:15:02,279
The whole family
acts so bland and spineless,

250
00:15:02,633 --> 00:15:04,460
like watered-down drinks.

251
00:15:04,460 --> 00:15:06,439
So I figured
at least I should be practical.

252
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:09,119
- I'm home.
- Hey.

253
00:15:10,393 --> 00:15:11,560
Everyone's gathered here.

254
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:13,860
Good timing.
We needed an emergency family meeting.

255
00:15:14,793 --> 00:15:16,416
You too, sit down here.

256
00:15:16,819 --> 00:15:18,985
What nonsense are you about to say
this time?

257
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:21,520
Why are you acting all dramatic?

258
00:15:22,420 --> 00:15:24,860
So,
did you clearly express your intentions?

259
00:15:24,860 --> 00:15:26,459
Of course.

260
00:15:26,893 --> 00:15:28,695
I got straight to the point.

261
00:15:28,939 --> 00:15:30,964
"Let's collaborate."

262
00:15:31,613 --> 00:15:34,093
I even bought her a slice of cake
with money I barely had,

263
00:15:34,779 --> 00:15:36,602
drew an impressive webtoon panel
and gave it to her,

264
00:15:37,272 --> 00:15:39,338
and practically begged
while trying everything I could.

265
00:15:39,839 --> 00:15:41,460
Begged?

266
00:15:41,460 --> 00:15:44,151
You punk. After I fed you a warm meal...

267
00:15:45,260 --> 00:15:47,665
You think that was truly your best effort?

268
00:15:47,665 --> 00:15:50,793
Of course. What more can I do?

269
00:15:50,793 --> 00:15:51,940
I have my pride too.

270
00:15:53,019 --> 00:15:57,093
You're talking about pride.
I guess you're not truly desperate.

271
00:15:57,093 --> 00:15:59,199
No, I am desperate.

272
00:15:59,199 --> 00:16:01,241
I'm really, really desperate.

273
00:16:01,892 --> 00:16:03,055
Then do more.

274
00:16:03,765 --> 00:16:07,066
Do everything you can
until you have no shame left.

275
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:11,171
And if it still doesn't work out,
then give up cleanly after that.

276
00:16:12,407 --> 00:16:14,850
That way, you won't be left
with regret or lingering feelings.

277
00:16:18,513 --> 00:16:20,530
What does "do everything I can" even mean?

278
00:16:20,766 --> 00:16:23,234
What? Be more specific. Make it easy.

279
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:25,604
Can I go now?

280
00:16:25,604 --> 00:16:28,464
Seriously. Are you really my sister?

281
00:16:28,786 --> 00:16:30,957
Your only younger brother's life
is on the line here.

282
00:16:30,957 --> 00:16:33,589
I think Dad already gave you
enough advice.

283
00:16:34,052 --> 00:16:35,228
- Get some rest.
- Okay.

284
00:16:35,228 --> 00:16:36,295
Hey, Seo Seung Ri.

285
00:16:36,632 --> 00:16:39,732
I'm only letting this slide today,

286
00:16:40,460 --> 00:16:42,034
considering the state
you've been in lately.

287
00:16:42,034 --> 00:16:43,302
What state?

288
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:45,171
You haven't been normal lately.

289
00:16:45,660 --> 00:16:47,893
Hurry up and go back
to being the old Seo Seung Ri.

290
00:16:47,893 --> 00:16:50,576
I haven't been beating you these days,
have I?

291
00:16:50,576 --> 00:16:54,046
There we go. That's it.
Now that's the real Seo Seung Ri.

292
00:16:54,299 --> 00:16:56,248
Player Seo Seung Ri
is full of fighting spirit.

293
00:16:58,152 --> 00:16:59,252
Forget it.

294
00:17:00,793 --> 00:17:01,921
Don't mess with your sister.

295
00:17:13,766 --> 00:17:15,601
How's Mom?

296
00:17:16,320 --> 00:17:17,720
She fell asleep a little while ago.

297
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:19,939
Don't worry too much, Dad.

298
00:17:20,679 --> 00:17:24,243
Mom will come around eventually,
though it may take some time.

299
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:28,348
Your mom must be devastated.

300
00:17:28,999 --> 00:17:33,218
Especially after being betrayed so badly
by the person she trusted most.

301
00:17:35,013 --> 00:17:38,509
Dad, I understand that frustration
better than anyone.

302
00:17:41,293 --> 00:17:43,923
What now? Did something happen
between you and Ji Seon?

303
00:17:44,779 --> 00:17:46,416
No. I'll handle my own problems.

304
00:17:46,973 --> 00:17:48,501
Just take good care of Mom for now.

305
00:17:49,036 --> 00:17:50,636
Dad, I should get going.

306
00:17:52,020 --> 00:17:54,006
I'm sorry. For everything.

307
00:17:54,113 --> 00:17:55,875
Don't be.

308
00:17:56,253 --> 00:17:58,511
Dad, hold your shoulders up high, okay?

309
00:17:58,912 --> 00:18:01,380
All right. Now hurry and go.

310
00:18:02,293 --> 00:18:05,046
Dad, I'm going to take a walk.
Want to come with me?

311
00:18:05,860 --> 00:18:09,025
No. You go ahead.
I should stay by your mom's side.

312
00:18:09,699 --> 00:18:11,453
- I'll get going.
- Okay.

313
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:31,644
She said she lives around here somewhere.

314
00:18:33,546 --> 00:18:36,182
(Our Happy Days Real Estate Agency,
Kang Yeon Ja)

315
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,252
Our Happy Days?

316
00:18:43,560 --> 00:18:44,893
You're Team Manager Ko Gyeol, right?

317
00:18:44,893 --> 00:18:46,525
Yes, hello.

318
00:18:47,593 --> 00:18:48,894
But what brings you here?

319
00:18:49,293 --> 00:18:52,365
I doubt you came
because you missed our bindaetteok.

320
00:18:53,293 --> 00:18:55,293
Well, I was just passing by.

321
00:18:55,293 --> 00:18:59,305
Passing by? Come on, I know everything.

322
00:18:59,305 --> 00:19:01,774
Excuse me? Know what exactly?

323
00:19:02,260 --> 00:19:04,160
- You came to see Eun Ae, right?
- What?

324
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:06,078
You already saw her at work today,

325
00:19:07,453 --> 00:19:08,814
and you already miss her?

326
00:19:09,186 --> 00:19:11,450
- Should I tell her to come out?
- No, it's fine.

327
00:19:11,450 --> 00:19:14,120
I came because there's something urgent
I needed to discuss with her,

328
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:16,680
but now that I think about it,
we can talk tomorrow at work.

329
00:19:16,860 --> 00:19:18,190
Then I'll...

330
00:19:19,346 --> 00:19:20,960
- Ms. Cho Eun Ae.
- Team Manager.

331
00:19:21,879 --> 00:19:24,864
I had something urgent to discuss
about the presentation.

332
00:19:25,580 --> 00:19:28,834
Sure. I'll excuse myself then.

333
00:19:29,260 --> 00:19:30,870
Go ahead with your urgent discussion.

334
00:19:33,093 --> 00:19:34,093
What's with her?

335
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:37,543
Why is she so excited?

336
00:19:39,260 --> 00:19:41,660
You came because of
the retirement community's name?

337
00:19:42,293 --> 00:19:45,160
Yes. Everything else is nearly finished,

338
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:47,260
but we still haven't decided
on the most important thing, the name.

339
00:19:47,260 --> 00:19:50,339
You could've just texted or called,

340
00:19:50,339 --> 00:19:51,857
or we could've discussed it
tomorrow at work.

341
00:19:52,206 --> 00:19:54,093
Well, I was worried.

342
00:19:54,326 --> 00:19:56,393
I wondered
if you had some trouble at home.

343
00:19:57,198 --> 00:19:58,964
Why are you worrying about me?

344
00:19:59,601 --> 00:20:02,281
If the team manager doesn't worry
about the team member, then who will?

345
00:20:03,060 --> 00:20:05,160
If you're distracted by other things,
you won't be able to focus.

346
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:06,872
And then it'll affect the competition too.

347
00:20:06,872 --> 00:20:08,630
Right.

348
00:20:09,093 --> 00:20:11,043
Now you show your true feelings.

349
00:20:12,093 --> 00:20:15,762
Don't worry. I won't cause concern
over personal matters anymore.

350
00:20:16,946 --> 00:20:20,309
More importantly,
I just thought of a good name.

351
00:20:20,893 --> 00:20:23,710
I got the idea from the real estate sign
in front of that bindaetteok place.

352
00:20:24,213 --> 00:20:26,653
For our retirement community name,
"Our Happy"...

353
00:20:26,653 --> 00:20:27,760
- "Good Home."
- "Good Home?"

354
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:29,962
- Jinx.
- What?

355
00:20:32,346 --> 00:20:34,600
- Sorry.
- You're seriously strange.

356
00:20:36,927 --> 00:20:38,871
The more I come here,
the more I like Jeongdam-dong.

357
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:42,842
My neighborhood's great, right?
Friendly people and clean water.

358
00:20:43,492 --> 00:20:45,344
- That's why it's called Jeongdam-dong.
- Exactly.

359
00:21:01,519 --> 00:21:02,995
Honey, I'm heading to work.

360
00:21:06,213 --> 00:21:08,066
I'm going to quit
the outsourcing company today.

361
00:21:08,635 --> 00:21:10,302
A week later,
I'll be Kangsu Construction's...

362
00:21:19,393 --> 00:21:20,393
I'm off.

363
00:21:30,793 --> 00:21:31,860
Have a good day, Dad.

364
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:36,962
Did you sleep well, Mom?

365
00:21:38,731 --> 00:21:40,566
That's a lot of bean sprouts.

366
00:21:41,093 --> 00:21:42,501
What, are we having a feast?

367
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:45,771
Just make your own breakfast
and get ready for work.

368
00:21:46,093 --> 00:21:49,475
Mom, please go easy on Dad, okay?

369
00:21:54,560 --> 00:21:55,881
Mom.

370
00:22:03,772 --> 00:22:06,460
Father, there's something I need to say.

371
00:22:06,460 --> 00:22:09,873
Why now, when you have to leave for work?
Sit down.

372
00:22:14,293 --> 00:22:15,635
Then talk.

373
00:22:21,792 --> 00:22:25,510
Father, I'm a little hurt.

374
00:22:26,573 --> 00:22:28,280
I'm your only son, right?

375
00:22:28,913 --> 00:22:32,251
Get to the point.
Stop beating around the bush.

376
00:22:32,716 --> 00:22:35,800
I already know that you've been searching
for someone...

377
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:36,833
through Mr. Seo lately.

378
00:22:39,133 --> 00:22:40,707
Why does Mr. Seo know secrets...

379
00:22:40,707 --> 00:22:43,762
that even I, your own son, don't know?

380
00:22:44,093 --> 00:22:48,293
Well now. If I'm not telling you,

381
00:22:48,293 --> 00:22:50,002
then there must be a good reason for it.

382
00:22:50,002 --> 00:22:53,038
No matter how much you trust Mr. Seo,
he's still an outsider.

383
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:54,440
Ko Dae Chi.

384
00:22:55,659 --> 00:22:58,978
Do you really not know
what you should be focusing on right now?

385
00:23:00,246 --> 00:23:02,314
What I should be doing?

386
00:23:03,593 --> 00:23:05,851
You should be thinking
about how to lead the company well,

387
00:23:06,293 --> 00:23:09,157
so that my absence isn't felt,
no matter what.

388
00:23:09,660 --> 00:23:10,890
What is this,
first thing in the morning...

389
00:23:12,593 --> 00:23:16,360
So what you mean is,
as the future chairman, I should...

390
00:23:16,360 --> 00:23:19,665
- Hey now.
- Yes, understood.

391
00:23:20,325 --> 00:23:23,832
I'll make sure there's no chance
for anyone to even feel your absence.

392
00:23:23,832 --> 00:23:25,132
I'll lead things properly.

393
00:23:27,293 --> 00:23:28,293
I'm heading to work now.

394
00:23:39,080 --> 00:23:41,788
Sit down. I have something to say.

395
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:44,560
To me?

396
00:23:49,752 --> 00:23:51,103
What is it?

397
00:23:54,903 --> 00:23:57,349
I'm sorry for losing my temper last time.

398
00:23:59,160 --> 00:24:02,441
You kept searching our room,
so I misunderstood.

399
00:24:02,993 --> 00:24:05,144
Are you apologizing to me right now?

400
00:24:08,217 --> 00:24:11,432
Mother, that photo...
It's your daughter, isn't it?

401
00:24:12,425 --> 00:24:13,525
- What?
- Well...

402
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,854
I'll keep it secret,
so just tell me quietly.

403
00:24:16,089 --> 00:24:17,156
Su Jeong.

404
00:24:17,460 --> 00:24:20,453
Come on, I'm not completely clueless.

405
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:23,093
Father touched that photo, didn't he?

406
00:24:23,819 --> 00:24:25,719
Well then, I guess
it's not much of a secret after all.

407
00:24:27,093 --> 00:24:30,960
I forgot I shouldn't talk too much
with you.

408
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:40,212
She was apologizing to me a moment ago,
so why is she suddenly reacting like that?

409
00:24:47,793 --> 00:24:50,393
Did you sleep well?
I made breakfast for you.

410
00:24:51,613 --> 00:24:53,425
I applied for an office position.

411
00:24:53,593 --> 00:24:55,560
I'll only be on line duty
until this month,

412
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:56,958
and starting next month,
I'll work in the management team.

413
00:24:57,293 --> 00:24:59,199
An office position? Why all of a sudden?

414
00:24:59,199 --> 00:25:00,866
You said you'll be teaching
five days a week.

415
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:04,260
If I'm away from home all the time too,
what will happen to Bit Na?

416
00:25:05,966 --> 00:25:08,640
Mother hasn't really been paying attention
to us lately either.

417
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:11,160
So does that mean
you'll be home every day now?

418
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:14,160
Yeah. I'll go to work in the morning
and come home in the evening.

419
00:25:14,393 --> 00:25:16,457
No more being away from home for days.

420
00:25:16,815 --> 00:25:18,315
Awesome.

421
00:25:18,993 --> 00:25:21,160
Thank you, honey.
Seriously, thank you so much.

422
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:24,957
No need to thank me.
I'm only giving up my flight allowance.

423
00:25:27,439 --> 00:25:30,239
By the way, did something happen
at your mother's place?

424
00:25:31,926 --> 00:25:33,198
Yeah, sort of.

425
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:34,960
What happened?

426
00:25:36,512 --> 00:25:37,893
Or is it something I shouldn't know about?

427
00:25:37,893 --> 00:25:40,172
Even if you knew,
it wouldn't change anything.

428
00:25:40,973 --> 00:25:43,275
There. All done.

429
00:25:43,493 --> 00:25:45,477
You really have golden hands, Dad.

430
00:25:45,593 --> 00:25:46,678
- High five.
- High five.

431
00:25:46,678 --> 00:25:48,914
(Kangsu Construction)

432
00:25:50,193 --> 00:25:54,286
Everyone, attention.
I have an announcement.

433
00:25:54,399 --> 00:25:57,923
The Chairman will also be attending
this judging.

434
00:25:59,758 --> 00:26:02,528
Are all brochures and briefing materials
for each team ready?

435
00:26:02,528 --> 00:26:05,160
Team One is perfectly prepared.

436
00:26:05,639 --> 00:26:07,599
Our team will finish everything by today.

437
00:26:07,760 --> 00:26:10,421
Team Two, gather in the conference room.
Let's run a simulation.

438
00:26:10,646 --> 00:26:11,646
Yes.

439
00:26:13,940 --> 00:26:16,406
The atmosphere here is intense.

440
00:26:17,193 --> 00:26:19,545
Should we run
one more final simulation too?

441
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:21,360
Do we really need to?

442
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:23,693
Team One is already perfection itself.

443
00:26:23,693 --> 00:26:25,160
Our team still has a lot to do.

444
00:26:25,746 --> 00:26:28,593
We're going to revise the slogan
and branding again,

445
00:26:28,593 --> 00:26:32,491
and we'll also add sub copy
in addition to the main copy.

446
00:26:32,806 --> 00:26:34,356
What is this?

447
00:26:34,693 --> 00:26:37,129
At this rate, our team's heading
for another all-nighter too.

448
00:26:39,706 --> 00:26:42,768
I'm thinking of widening the hallway
by about ten centimeters...

449
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:45,460
to better secure the spatial layout
so that two wheelchairs...

450
00:26:45,460 --> 00:26:47,060
can pass through at the same time.

451
00:26:48,060 --> 00:26:51,460
But then the number of units
will decrease accordingly.

452
00:26:51,460 --> 00:26:54,460
We're not building homes we want to sell.

453
00:26:54,460 --> 00:26:56,148
We're building homes
people want to live in.

454
00:26:57,560 --> 00:26:59,360
- Right.
- And also,

455
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:01,053
what kind of tree should we plant
in the courtyard?

456
00:27:01,993 --> 00:27:05,691
How about fruit trees
like persimmon, jujube, or apple trees?

457
00:27:05,860 --> 00:27:07,560
So the residents
can grow them themselves...

458
00:27:07,560 --> 00:27:09,967
and enjoy harvesting them too.

459
00:27:09,967 --> 00:27:12,231
And what about a herb garden nearby?

460
00:27:12,998 --> 00:27:16,335
That sounds good. We could even add
a small vegetable garden.

461
00:27:16,660 --> 00:27:17,660
A vegetable garden?

462
00:27:18,673 --> 00:27:21,237
Wouldn't that feel a little too rural?

463
00:27:21,492 --> 00:27:25,410
That's our concept. Nature,
countryside, a hometown-like feeling.

464
00:27:30,780 --> 00:27:32,351
It's okay. Take it.

465
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:35,760
Eun Nim, what is it?

466
00:27:36,352 --> 00:27:40,358
Something terrible happened. Mom...

467
00:27:40,626 --> 00:27:41,693
What about Mom?

468
00:27:43,160 --> 00:27:44,160
What?

469
00:28:08,620 --> 00:28:11,623
(Our Happy Days)

470
00:28:11,823 --> 00:28:14,326
- Still no word from Mom?
- No.

471
00:28:14,326 --> 00:28:17,429
All of us betrayed Mom,

472
00:28:17,429 --> 00:28:19,331
yet she worried about us
until the very end.

473
00:28:19,331 --> 00:28:22,631
Kang Yeon Ja, how is this
the only place you could come to?

474
00:28:22,631 --> 00:28:25,137
Are you really the kind of person
who ties someone else's shoelaces?

475
00:28:25,137 --> 00:28:27,039
How do you think
the person seeing that would feel?

476
00:28:27,039 --> 00:28:29,374
I'm fine, so stop trying so hard.

477
00:28:29,374 --> 00:28:31,560
Let's video call.

478
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:32,911
Video call?

479
00:28:33,178 --> 00:28:34,780
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
